FBIS3-51814 "drlat016_b_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 Bermuda Haiti Parliamentary Leader Defends Public Security Government FL2401223094 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in Creole 1230 GMT 24 Jan 94 FL2401223094 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio Language: Creole Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] All those who disagree with the resolution of the Group of the Great North [Collectif des Citoyens du Grand Nord, CCGN], must remain exiled in their own country. This was said by Herve Leveille who criticized those who said they are not members of the national congress, which has established a government of public security in the country, [and who say that the government] is not legitimate. In a message published over the weekend, Leveille rebukes those who say the national congress people did not have the Haitian people's support. [Begin recording, in French] [passage omitted] Active and peaceful mobilization is ordered throughout the Haitian territory. Active and peaceful mobilization is ordered throughout the Haitian territory. [repeats] The watchword has been released, so our intentions can be respected, so those who say no to rebirth and salvation can be exiled in their own country. [passage omitted] Determined, we will come home to continue the patriotic struggle with all the means we have at our disposal. To do this, we will leave in place the office that conducted our works and helped us look inward so we could say no to the premeditated failure of an entire people. [end recording]
